(-4)^n
\sum_{k=0}^{4n} \binom{4n}{k} i^k = (1+i)^{4n} = \left(\sqrt{2} e^{i \pi /4}\right)^{4n} = 4^n e^{i n \pi} = 4^n \left(\cos (n \pi) + i\sin (n \pi)\right) = (-4)^n.
\sum_{k=0}^{2n} \binom{4n}{2k} (-1)^k = (-4)^n
\sum_{k=0}^{2n-1} \binom{4n}{2k+1} (-1)^k = 0.
